tempest/api/identity/v3/test_api_discove.message:
Why do we need such complex function here?
We just want to check the existence of v3 API in version API based on the configuration. So here can be just

 def test_identity_v3_existence(self):
     versions = self.non_admin_versions_client.list_versions()
     found = False
     for version in versions['versions']["values"]:
         if "v3" in version.get('id'):
             found = True
     if CONF.identity_feature_enabled.api_v3:
         self.assertTrue(found)

